      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/98/6",
      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُ أَبَا جَعْفَرٍ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنْ رَجُلٍ مَاتَ وَ لَمْ يَحُجَّ حَجَّةَ اَلْإِسْلاَمِ وَ لَمْ يُوصِ بِهَا أَ يُقْضَى عَنْهُ قَالَ «نَعَمْ»."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2922 - It was narrated from Asim ibn Humayd, from Muhammad ibn Muslim, who said:\nI asked Abu Ja'far (as) about a man who died without performing the Hajj of Islam and did not include it in his will. Should it be performed on his behalf?\nImam (as) said: \"Yes.\""
        ]
      }
    },
